SIMPLE: animalize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Animalize
<hw>An"i*mal*ize</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Animalized</conjf>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Animalizing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>animaliser</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To endow with the
properties of an animal; to represent in animal form.</def>
<rj><au>Warburton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To convert into animal matter by the processes of
assimilation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To render animal or sentient; to reduce to the state
of a lower animal; to sensualize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The unconscious irony of the Epicurean poet on the
<qex>animalizing</qex> tendency of his own philosophy.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Animally</ent>⟦br⟧
